<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25696</anchor> <rss>anon.177.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.177</addr>  <route>anon.177.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>To identify two witnesses <tex>\phi , \phi '  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } x = y</tex> that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, it suffices via the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">pointwise univalent univalence principle for functions</link> to exhibit a double homotopy in <tex>A</tex> identifying each <tex>\phi  xy</tex> with <tex>\phi 'xy</tex>. As <link href="erct-001L.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001L" title="Propositions are sets">propositions are sets</link>, this follows from our assumption that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25697</anchor> <rss>erct-001O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001O</addr>  <route>erct-001O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001O.agda" type="external">erct-001O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25698</anchor> <rss>erct-001L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001L</addr>  <route>erct-001L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">Propositions</link> are <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">sets</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001L.agda" type="external">erct-001L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25699</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Propositions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25700</anchor> <rss>erct-0015.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-0015</addr>  <route>erct-0015.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The univalence principle for dependent functions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0015.agda" type="external">erct-0015.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The reflexive graph structure on <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } {Bx}</tex> by <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> and <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">identity homotopies</link> is <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">univalent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>